Moving from Traditional Syntax to Scala
Example-Finding Odd or Even
Case 1- Find whether a number is odd or even
 Scala- def oddEven(n:Int):Boolean=n%2==0
 //For a list of even Numbers in the range m to n-
  def oddEvenRange(m:Int,n:Int):IndexedSeq[Int]=for(i<- m to n filter ((i:Int)=>i % 2 == 0)) yield i
 
Traditional-
public static Boolean checkEvenOdd(Int n){
if(n%2 == 0){return true}
else{return false}}
